# Spring Boot Actuator

## Endpoint Exposure

### Default: Expose Only What You Need
```yaml
management:
  endpoints:
    web:
      exposure:
        include: health, info, metrics, prometheus
  endpoint:
    health:
      show-details: when-authorized
      probes:
        enabled: true
  info:
    env:
      enabled: true
```

### NEVER in Production
- `management.endpoints.web.exposure.include: "*"` -- exposes env, beans, configprops, heapdump
- Unsecured `/actuator/env` leaks secrets
- Unsecured `/actuator/heapdump` leaks entire heap including credentials

### Security
```java
@Bean
public SecurityFilterChain actuatorSecurity(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
    return http
        .securityMatcher("/actuator/**")
        .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
            .requestMatchers("/actuator/health/**").permitAll()
            .requestMatchers("/actuator/info").permitAll()
            .requestMatchers("/actuator/prometheus").permitAll()
            .anyRequest().hasRole("ACTUATOR_ADMIN")
        )
        .httpBasic(Customizer.withDefaults())
        .build();
}
```

## Health Indicators

### Built-in
Spring Boot auto-configures: `db` (DataSource), `diskSpace`, `redis`, `mail`, `jms`, `rabbit`.

### Custom Health Indicator
```java
@Component
public class PaymentGatewayHealthIndicator implements HealthIndicator {

    private final PaymentGatewayClient client;

    @Override
    public Health health() {
        try {
            client.ping();
            return Health.up()
                .withDetail("gateway", "reachable")
                .build();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return Health.down()
                .withDetail("gateway", "unreachable")
                .withException(e)
                .build();
        }
    }
}
```

### Kubernetes Probes
```yaml
management:
  endpoint:
    health:
      probes:
        enabled: true
      group:
        liveness:
          include: livenessState
        readiness:
          include: readinessState, db, redis
```
- **Liveness** (`/actuator/health/liveness`): Is the JVM alive? Restart if DOWN.
- **Readiness** (`/actuator/health/readiness`): Can the app serve traffic? Remove from LB if DOWN.

## Custom Metrics (Micrometer)

### Counter (events)
```java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    private final Counter orderCounter;

    public OrderService(MeterRegistry registry) {
        this.orderCounter = Counter.builder("orders.created")
            .description("Total orders created")
            .tag("type", "api")
            .register(registry);
    }

    public Order createOrder(OrderRequest request) {
        var order = /* ... */;
        orderCounter.increment();
        return order;
    }
}
```

### Timer (latency)
```java
@Around("@annotation(Timed)")
public Object time(ProceedingJoinPoint pjp) throws Throwable {
    return Timer.builder("service.method.duration")
        .tag("class", pjp.getTarget().getClass().getSimpleName())
        .tag("method", pjp.getSignature().getName())
        .register(meterRegistry)
        .record(() -> {
            try { return pjp.proceed(); }
            catch (Throwable t) { throw new RuntimeException(t); }
        });
}
```

### Gauge (current value)
```java
@Bean
public MeterBinder queueSizeGauge(TaskQueue taskQueue) {
    return registry -> Gauge.builder("task.queue.size", taskQueue, TaskQueue::size)
        .description("Current task queue depth")
        .register(registry);
}
```

## Tagging Conventions
- Use lowercase, dot-separated names: `orders.created`, `http.server.requests`
- Low-cardinality tags only: `status`, `method`, `outcome`
- **NEVER** tag with user IDs, request IDs, or other high-cardinality values

## Info Endpoint
```yaml
info:
  app:
    name: "@project.name@"
    version: "@project.version@"
    java: ${java.version}
    spring-boot: "@spring-boot.version@"
```

## Prometheus Export
```yaml
management:
  prometheus:
    metrics:
      export:
        enabled: true
```
Endpoint: `/actuator/prometheus` (Prometheus scrape target).

## Management Port Separation
For sensitive production environments, separate Actuator from application traffic:
```yaml
management:
  server:
    port: 9090
```
